Description.Text: This 4-star hotel is considered to be a first-class property. It is exceptionally well-located in Paris. In this charming Parisian hotel even if the decor would benefit from a renovation it is a still a very good value for money. You will enjoy the kindness of the team and benefit from its location, close to all the shops and main spots of the capital. (1110ADB)

The hotel is located in the famous Rue Faubourg St. Honore, an elegant district, next to Place de Madeleine, close to the Place de La Concorde, Champs Elysees and American and British Embassies. There is good public transport close to the hotel.

The rooms are medium in size, with traditional decor. The rooms are well-equipped, with television, mini-bar, safe and hairdryers. Some standard rooms have a small balcony, with a view onto Sacre Coeur and Paris rooftops.
The hotel is housed in an elegant and traditional 8-storey, Parisian "art deco" style building.
The restaurant is on the ground floor. It is chic and modern, with black-based Bordeaux decor. Refined French cuisine is served by efficient staff.

The lobby and entrance are small but welcoming, with its wooden reception desk and 1930's style. The lobby opens onto the lounge area, the decor of which is tasteful, with red and green modern candle shades.
